    <div class="container mt-5">
      <div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-center">
        <h5 class="text-center">Freedom Wall Rule: Respectful Expression</h5>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          Rule: All posts on the Freedom Wall must be respectful and
          constructive. Please adhere to the following guidelines:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          1. Respectful Language: Use language that is considerate of others.
          Avoid hate speech, discriminatory remarks, or personal attacks.
          Respect diverse opinions and experiences.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          2. Constructive Feedback: When engaging with others' posts, provide
          feedback that is helpful and constructive. Aim to contribute to
          meaningful discussions rather than arguments.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          3. Privacy and Safety: Do not share personal information about
          yourself or others without consent. Respect the privacy of fellow
          users and refrain from posting content that could jeopardize someone's
          safety.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          4. No Spam or Self-Promotion: Avoid posting repetitive content or
          using the Freedom Wall for self-promotion or spamming. Focus on
          contributing valuable content to the community.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          5. Report Violations: If you come across content that violates these
          rules, please report it to the moderators for review. Your cooperation
          helps maintain a positive environment.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
          Why This Rule Matters: These guidelines help create a supportive and
          engaging space where everyone feels safe to express their thoughts and
          ideas. By following these rules, you contribute to a community that
          values respect and meaningful conversation.
        </p>
